Text.SourceString: There’s a whole different world down there. The more I dive, the more I see this island’s full potential.
You see a lot of debris from the past in the ocean, too.//A buried story, if you will.
<NPCName>Jim</> makes a delicious smoked salmon. He’s a big fan of smoked salmon, so you know…//<portrait=happy>He knows what makes it good!
I sell some fishing supplies. Oh, and we sometimes make fresh seafood meals.//<portrait=laugh>Don’t count on it, though!
No, they’re very good. It’s just that we don’t always make them.//And the menu changes, depending on what we have on hand.

The healthier the coral reefs, the more fish they attract…//<portrait=happy>Now, that’s just my observation… I don’t know enough about it to tell you why.//<portrait=normal><NPCName>Ling</> might be able to help with that.
Our lures and food containers are biodegradable. If they’re thrown out at sea, they can safely break down and return to nature.
It’s important to pay attention to our garbage.//I’ve seen too many turtles and other animals trapped in plastic.
Our lures and food containers are biodegradable. If they’re thrown out at sea, they can safely break down and return to nature.
It’s important to pay attention to our garbage.//I’ve seen too many turtles and other animals trapped in plastic.
How’s your Thursday going so far?
Ah, the beach… Never gets old.//<portrait=normal>Thankfully, <NPCName>Oliver</> loves the beach as much as he loves ice cream…//<portrait=happy>He gets that from me.
Uh-huh… <NPCName>Jim</> helps me run the shack. He also helped me decorate the interior.
He has good taste, eh?
There’s a whole different world down there. The more I dive, the more I see this island’s full potential.
You see a lot of debris from the past in the ocean, too.//A buried story, if you will.

The healthier the coral reefs, the more fish they attract…//<portrait=happy>Now, that’s just my observation… I don’t know enough about it to tell you why.//<portrait=normal><NPCName>Ling</> might be able to help with that.
I sell some fishing supplies. Oh, and we sometimes make fresh seafood meals.//<portrait=laugh>Don’t count on it, though!
No, they’re very good. It’s just that we don’t always make them.//And the menu changes, depending on what we have on hand.
Uh-huh… <NPCName>Jim</> helps me run the shack. He also helped me decorate the interior.
He has good taste, eh?
Ah, the beach… Never gets old.//<portrait=normal>Thankfully, <NPCName>Oliver</> loves the beach as much as he loves ice cream…//<portrait=happy>He gets that from me.

The new farmer! Hello! My name is <NPCName>Sunny</>. My friend <NPCName>Jim</> and I run this place…//<portrait=normal>My son, <NPCName>Oliver</>, is usually out there, playing on the beach. He’s the small one with blond hair.//The bigger lad on the boat is <NPCName>Jim’s</> boy.
Thanks for stopping by! Can I get you anything?
The new farmer! Hello… My name is <NPCName>Sunny</>.//<portrait=happy>My friend <NPCName>Jim</> and I run the best seafood place in town. Heh, heh.
Make sure to mention it to <NPCName>Frank</> when you see him, will you? Heh, heh!//<portrait=normal>Well, come by the shack if you need help with fishing. We’re on the beach.
Happy Summer! It’s the perfect weather to put on your wet suit and dive in, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Explore what’s down there… Aren’t you curious?
It’s nice and sunny today…//<portrait=laugh>Ha! Feels weird to say my name out loud.
I don’t mind a little bit of breeze and all that sort.
I try to take <NPCName>Oliver</> to school on rainy days. Make sure he doesn’t slip and all that.
I’m trying to stay indoors as much as I can.// Just don’t like the rain that much.
I decided to take the day off and have a nice hot tea.
Are you trying to keep warm too? I don’t blame you.//<portrait=concerned>I’m wearing this, and I’m still cold.
I don’t know all of them, but there are fish that only come out during the rain.
There are also fish that prefer to swim in the evening. Keep that in mind, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Something soupy might do tonight.
I’ll just make a pot, and I can eat some tomorrow too.
I try to take <NPCName>Oliver</> to school on rainy days. Make sure he doesn’t slip and all that.
I’m trying to stay indoors as much as I can.// Just don’t like the rain that much.
I decided to take the day off and have a nice hot tea.
Are you trying to keep warm too? I don’t blame you.//<portrait=concerned>I’m wearing this, and I’m still cold.
Look at this storm. It’s worrisome.
The wind was so loud last night… It woke me up, and I usually sleep like a log.//<portrait=concerned>Thankfully, it didn’t wake <NPCName>Oliver</> up.
We rarely get visitors from that part of the island. Too far to walk, I think…
I understand. My knees aren’t exactly shiny and new these days.
It’s a nice change to relax here once in a while.
For one, it’s a change of scenery.//<portrait=laugh><NPCName>Frank</> here is definitely a sight for sore eyes. Hear that, <NPCName>Frank</>?!
Oh, you’re here early.
Ahem… The lot over there is a pretty good spot if you want to find flowers.
Are you hunting for mushrooms?
It’s nice to catch a bit of sun out here before it sets.
You can always tell when the big fish are out. There’s a certain smell coming from the water.
Maybe it’s just the smell of a thousand fish, though.
The Tavern makes the most fantastic tea. When I was your age, I enjoyed the harder stuff more than tea, but you really ought to give it a try.
Try going tonight! It’ll be a little less crowded since it’s not a weekend.
The breeze feels wonderful today. Maybe I should take a walk on the beach.
Wait a second, <PlayerName>$player</>. What’s that behind your ear?
Looks like a coin! Now where did that come from?
I guess that one probably works better on <NPCName>Oliver</>.
Since I took <NPCName>Oliver</> to school today, I decided to get some tacos!
I need to ask <NPCName>Emma</> where she gets her fish. The tacos were great!
How’s life on the farm?
I remember sitting in the sun for hours when I used to fish. Sometimes I’d jump in the water and scare away all the fish just so I could cool off.
You ought to do something fun today, <PlayerName>$player</>! Like the kids say, you have to treat yourself!
I know <NPCName>Ollie</> seems like a quiet kid, but he gets so excited when his favorite show comes on TV. It’s about a boy detective who solves mysteries.
I don’t pretend to understand all of it, but I try to watch it with him at least a few times a week. If he didn’t have to go to school, I think that’s all he’d do all day!
I know this place looks a little rough around the edges, but that’s the way I like it. It’s the Beach Shack, after all, not the Beach Mansion.
Heh heh. Beach Mansion…//<portrait=normal>Oh, come on! THAT was funny.
I think I’ll do something different when work ends today. Maybe I’ll take a walk around the lake or say hello to some folks in town. Sounds like a fun time to me!
You can always tell when the big fish are out. There’s a certain smell coming from the water.
Maybe it’s just the smell of a thousand fish, though.
I know this place looks a little rough around the edges, but that’s the way I like it. It’s the Beach Shack, after all, not the Beach Mansion.
Heh heh. Beach Mansion…//<portrait=normal>Oh, come on! THAT was funny.
The breeze feels wonderful today. Maybe I should take a walk on the beach.
I wonder if <NPCName>Oliver</> would ever consider taking surfing lessons. He’s getting pretty good on his own.
I wonder if <NPCName>Yuri</> or <NPCName>Sam</> will stop by today. I hope they do – I’ve been dying to play some chess recently.
It’s getting warmer and warmer every day! Soon, the surfers will be back out on the waves.
I’ve been thinking about what I should get for <NPCName>Ollie’s</> birthday. He really wants a new surfboard, but I saw a new Boy Detective shirt he might like.
Maybe I’ll just get him both. What’s wrong with a little spoiling every now and then?
I’ve lived on Coral Island my whole life, but seeing the trees and flowers bloom each year still dazzles me.
We’re lucky to live in such a beautiful world.
There’s nothing wrong with a little rain here and there. It certainly cools you off.
Rainy days were always events when I was younger. We’d have to haul the boat inside the shack so it didn’t get rusty.
You know what, I don’t know. Heh heh.//But it seemed to work.

Special.SourceString: Is this right? Sea water won’t rust a boat, but rain will?

Text.SourceString: Heh heh! Thanks.//It seemed like a good idea at the time.

Special.SourceString: That sounds like a lot of work. You’re very diligent!

Text.SourceString: Try fishing today, <PlayerName>$player</>! You never know what you’ll catch on a rainy day.
A day like this is perfect for a nice long round of chess.
<NPCName>Ollie</> always sleeps well on rainy nights. The sound really calms him.
It calms me, too!
I hope this rain clears up by tomorrow. <NPCName>Oliver</> really wanted to go surfing.
Even if it’s warm outside, rainy days make me crave tea and hot soup.
I was going to make something different for dinner tonight, but maybe I should just go for soup instead.
The sea is always angry on days like this. Even I wouldn’t risk fishing when the water’s that choppy.
I know I shouldn’t be out when the weather’s like this, but standing in storms always makes me feel so free.
You look a little waterlogged, <PlayerName>$player</>! Go home and dry off.
Today’s just one of those days when you have to batten down the hatches and keep yourself dry.
We’ve got quite the raging storm outside. Are you sure you can make it home in this weather?
Feel free to camp out in the shack if you need to. It’s a little sandy, but it’s better than being wet.
<PlayerName>$player</>! You look like you’ve seen a ghost. Is the storm really that bad?
[Sunny seems busy behind the counter.]
What am I watching? Oh, it’s nothing important. I just like to have something on in the background while I doze.
<NPCName>Frank</> and <NPCName>Noah</> have done an amazing job with this place. You can’t get better tea anywhere on the island.
The sea. What a majestic thing.
[Sunny is staring out over the water.]
